HEADWORD: Caviling
<hw>Cav"il*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Disposed to cavil; finding fault
without good reason. See <er>Captious</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His depreciatory and <qex>caviling</qex> criticism.</q>
<rj><qau>Lewis.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cavilingly</ent>⟦br⟧
